Commentary: 138kph, swinging away, he drives and gets a thick edge that flies safely through the vacant gully and carries beyond the circle to third man
138kph, yorker, right on the money, he just digs it out. Brilliant delivery and equally well played
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: 137kph, length ball across him, he flashes and misses trying to square drive
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: 138kph, fuller outside off, he mistimes a drive slowly to mid off and runs with the stroke
137kph, angled down leg, does he get a tickle or does it come off pad? Either way it fell short of Carey
137kph, angled into the hip, he jumps back and glances this to wide fine leg and they push for two but only get one
138kph, full and some swing into the left hander, he pushes a drive to mid on and takes a tight single
138kph, fuller outside off, he reaches away from his body and miscues a drive to mid off
Commentary_short: Abbott to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: 134kph, good length outside off, he tries to drive but drags it off the thick inside half off the bat through square leg to the sweeper
he shuffles down to a 140kph full inswinger, beaten for pace, it comes off the pad and rolls away. He was hit outside leg
beaten by a 138kph, good length wobbling in and seaming away outside off
he charges and lofts this over mid on! Didn't nail it. It was 138kph, shaping in a length and he shimmied down to turn it to a half volley. Good shot
140kph, fired down the leg side and called wide
swinging way down the leg side and rightly called wide again. Carey has to dive a long way
thumping square drive straight through Turner at point. It was a length ball and wide, he stands tall and crunches past Turner at point
Commentary_short: Starc to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: Given out LBW. He's been given and Babar reviews. This was full and shaping into the pad late. There was a big appeal and it carried to slip. There's no bat involved. Nothing on hot spot. RTS appears to say pad only. Daylight between bat and ball. Ball tracking is a little slow. We have to wait 30 seconds for ball tracking. Ball tracking says umpire's call! Clipping leg. It stays out LBW. It was just pitching in line and just clipping the outside of leg.
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam lbw b Starc 6 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 85.71

Commentary: Bowled him! Searing 140kph inswinger! This was like a heat-seeking missile. Started on off, swung late through a gaping gate as he tried to drive away from his body. His pads were outside leg, his bat outside off, the ball swerved through and crashed into middle and leg
142kph, good length outswinger on off, he pushes a drive to mid off
Commentary_short: Starc to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: 142kph, fuller length, no swing, he drives firmly back to the bowler and it comes off Starc and ricochets to mid off
Commentary_short: Starc to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: 138kph, bouncer and he ducks under it easily
Commentary_short: Starc to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: good length, hint of shape across him, he pushes a length ball to point
he charges early and it's banged in 131kph, into the ribs and he defends knocking it down
short on leg, he pulls to wide fine leg, they push hard for two on Abbott's arm and Imam has to dive to make it! They check upstairs but he's home just
137kph, short ball, over middle, he backs away and tries to uppercut but misses
137kph, short ball, he pulls and miscues off the top edge but it lands safely at the circle at midwicket
play and miss at a135kph length ball that swung away late
Commentary_short: Richardson to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: 132kph, length ball, top of off, he defends from the crease towards point
thumped straight over the umpire's head! 132kph, in the slot and he swings through the line and hammers it straight at the sightscreen

top edge caught at midwicket! Short ball banged in outside off, he tries to pull but goes from low to high with his hands, gets a top edge that flies straight up to midwicket, McDermott camps under it and takes the catch very easily. That was a poorly executed stroke
Dismissal_text: Imam-ul-Haq c McDermott b Abbott 14 (15b 2x4 0x6) SR: 93.33

Commentary: 135kph, good length fourth stump line, he pushes towards mid off
Commentary_short: Abbott to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: 132kph, back of a length, he pushes away from his body to backward point and Smith makes a superb diving save
Commentary_short: Abbott to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: 133kph, back of a length outside off, he's back and across and defending
Commentary_short: Abbott to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: back of a length on off, he stands up and defends
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: 144kph, full inswinger and he whips with the swing behind square Good shot. Conventional stroke, using the pace to ping it behind square
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: over-pitched wide of off, he opens the shoulder and hammers a cover drive. That was a half volley and he put it away easily
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: 141kph, fuller outside off, he tries to drive he miscues to mid on
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: 138kph, bouncer over leg, he half pulls half ducks, it flies through to Carey. No wide call
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: magnificent cover drive! Another long half volley and he leans forward to pound it through the big gap at cover.
Commentary_short: Starc to Iftikhar Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball into the ribs, he gets inside the line and works it around the corner to fine leg
134kph, short ball, climbing outside off, he tries to cut and it beats him for bounce
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: 142kph, fuller outside off, he drives hard and slices a thick outside edge high and wide of third man
thick edge nearly carries to third man! Richardson ran in off the rope and couldn't block the half volley. It was a good effort to try and catch it. That edge flew a long way
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: 138kph, back of a length on off, he defends to cover-point
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: 141kph, fuller on off, he drives back to the bowler, Stanlake deflects it onto the stumps at the non-strikers but Haris is back safely
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: fuller outside off, he drives firmly through cover straight of the man in the deep for a couple
91kph, shorter length, he's back and punching down to long off
arm ball drifting into leg, he's back and punching wide of long on, they push for two and beat the throw from Richardson. Good running
slower and shorter, with some spin, he's back and punching this to long on
102kph, low full toss, whipped to deep midwicket
shorter length, slid through at 98kph, he's back and cutting to backward point
Commentary_short: Agar to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: 147kph, over-pitched, he drives very nicely straight of mid off, Warner moves like a hare across the turf to dive and make the save
142kph, angled into leg, he glances this to fine leg with ease
142kph, bouncer, over leg stump, he ducks under it easily

Commentary: 140kph, bouncer, down the leg side and called wide
141kph, shorter length into the hip, he tucks this behind square for a single
135kph, over-pitched, he crunches a straight drive back and it comes off his boot and flies to mid on
138kph, shorter length, into the ribs, he tucks this to fine leg

caught at long off! That was brilliant from Agar. Haris jumped down early, Agar dragged the length down, Haris went through with the shot, mistimed it trying to launch over long off, he clothed it straight down Richardson's throat at long off. Easy catch 15 metres in off the rope
Dismissal_text: Haris Sohail c Richardson b Agar 8 (16b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: tossed up slower, he works with the turn towards long on, he pushes for two but it's not on
drifting into middle, he's back and working this through midwicket
drifting outside off, he drives, without timing past cover to the sweeper in the deep
tossed up, he pushes gently to cover point for one
shorter length, he's back and cutting to backward point
short of a length, thuds into Khushdil's chest, the pair scamper through for one

Commentary: pulled belligerently but no timing, straight to mid-on
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: cut away to third man. Stanlake is persisting with that short length, and doing a good job with it
fuller length, steered to midwicket
driven to mid-off, pair scuttle through for another quick single. This is good stuff from Australia
excellent over. Pakistan really going nowhere at the moment, and the pressure Iftikhar feels is understandable. His wicket could be the game

Commentary: chipper to long-off
straight back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Agar to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: the reverse sweep comes out. No timing, but that allows Pakistan to come back for two
guided past short cover-point for one
runs it to backward point for a single
poked to fine leg, and another tidy over concludes

this won't help improve their mood! Khushdil cleared his front leg and looked to tonk this into the stands behind midwicket. It went so high the keeper thought he might catch it, but in the end Starc at fine leg got himself into position and snared a swirling one. Pakistan lose half their side.
Dismissal_text: Khushdil Shah c Starc b Richardson 8 (11b 0x4 0x6) SR: 72.72

Commentary: short and wide, and finally a boundary comes! The width allowed Iftikhar to slash at it, and it races to the third man boundary

Commentary: better delivery, defended
Commentary_short: Richardson to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: short ball again, muscled to midwicket. Gets clean contact on that and they come back for two
cut straight to backward point
Commentary_short: Richardson to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: no control from the batsman, but it's four! Top edge that nearly carried all the way for six; when you're in form like Iftikhar is, everything goes your way. Turned out to be a decent over from Pakistan despite the wicket; they need to get a move on
Commentary_short: Richardson to Iftikhar Ahmed, FOUR runs

Commentary: cut away for one
poor delivery, gets away with it. Down legside, and Iftikhar gives it a slap, but fine leg is there to cut it off
no timing from Imad, but they come back for two
a whack down the ground, but again, got very little of the middle of the bat on it
guided to square leg, Agar has been so tight today. Fantastic spin bowling.
excellent over once more. Just what Australia needed after a slightly expensive one from Richardson
Imad goes down the ground, the length is dragged back, and he can only splice it to the onside for one
good timing, but Abbott is bowling short of a length at pace, and Iftikhar doesn't have enough time to get underneath it

gone! What a catch! Agar can't put a foot wrong today. Not a surprise, in truth. Nothing had been working for Imad in the short time he';d been there. I don't believe he middled a single ball. Similar shot to the previous one. Came down the pitch, and the length was too short for him to get any purchase on the shot. Agar sprinted forward to scoop it up inches from the ground
Dismissal_text: Imad Wasim c Agar b Abbott 6 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: Shadab nearly got himself run out. No communication between the two, and Shadab at the non-striker's end would have been gone with a direct hit
Commentary_short: Abbott to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: steered to third man
blocks and sets off rather aimlessly, Iftikhar knows better than to take him up on the offer.
Commentary_short: Abbott to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: Scooped into the vacant legside infield from Iftikhar. think he was looking to get it into a deserted enough area to come back for two
Pace and bounce. Lovely stuff from Stanlake. Tentative poke and a miss
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: Nudged to short backward point and Shadab gets himself off strike

excellent bowling again. Short and Iftikhar didn't quite know what to do with it. Lucky he didn't edge it straight back to the bowler. Almost comes back and hits his stumps, the batsman had to stop it with his bat
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: pulled to fine leg
makes room for himself and Stanlake throws it well outside off stump. Never quite in position to execute the extravagant cut, and it's another swing and a miss
Commentary_short: Stanlake to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: massive blow for Pakistan! Heaved down to fine leg from Iftikhar. He'd been struggling with the short ball for much of the innings, and Starc at fine leg was secure as ever. Richardson, who copped such heavy punishment from Iftikhar last game, get's his revenge
Dismissal_text: Iftikhar Ahmed c Starc b Richardson 45 (37b 6x4 0x6) SR: 121.62

Commentary: clattered straight to point
Commentary_short: Richardson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: swing and a miss. Shadab one off six now. Needs to kick on badly
Commentary_short: Richardson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: copy and paste. This time he tried a swivel-pull, but Carey gathers it behind the stumps again
Commentary_short: Richardson to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: the miserable innings comes to an end! Well, colour me surprised! Shadab had been struggling badly all eight balls he was there, and this time, he got a thick edge. Mid-on made a bit of a meal of it, but that's it for the allrounder
Dismissal_text: Shadab Khan c Finch b Richardson 1 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 12.50

Commentary: wow, what was that from Hasnain! No double wicket maiden for Richardson, as Hasnain middles his first ball for an exquisite cover drive that goes straight to the boundary! Watch and learn, Imad and Shadab, the teenager might meekly mutter to himself

Commentary: dragged down legside
backs away, does Amir, and tentatively times it back down the ground
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: that's better! First maximum of the night. Amir backs away again, but it was the shorter delivery that allowed Amir to get a thick edge on it, which carried all the way over the third man boundary
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Amir, SIX runs

Commentary: straight to the fielder
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: yorker, Amir digs it out and the pair change ends
he was barely in the same postcode. Looked to repeat the shot he played so well off Richardson, but the shorter length renders it impossible
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: yorker that just misses leg stump
Commentary_short: Starc to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: run down to third man
wild swing from Hasnain, but Richardson says 'I deserve more respect' with a ball that flummoxes the number 10 completely
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: Carbon copy. Hasnain might have to consider descending from cloud nine, where he might still be after that lovely cover drive first ball. Needs to rotate the strike
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: but who cares what I think? Another lavish swing, another obvious miss. One off four balls this over
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: four in a row. Nothing connecting for Hasnain now, and Amir can only watch from the other end
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: swing and a miss. Hasnain has clearly decided that is all he wants to do. top stuff from Richardson. Just one off that over
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: short ball, Amir ducks below it
Commentary_short: Abbott to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: Amir backed away to try and cut it through the covers. Misses again. That's seven balls in a row the bat hasn't made contact with the ball

Commentary: make that eight! Amir looks to scoop this over fine leg. Doesn't even make contact with it
Commentary_short: Abbott to Mohammad Amir, no run

Commentary: hallelujah, there's bat on ball! And there's even a ticking over of the scores. They take a single. A SINGLE! What will Australia do now?
Hasnain swings like a rusty gate, as they say these days. Just one off five balls this final over
Commentary_short: Abbott to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: and ends, predictably, with another miss. Two off the final two overs, and on a miserable evening in Perth, Pakistan limp to 106. They trudge off, no sign of a spring in their step, while Australia are practically prancing off the field. This should be comfortable for them
Commentary_short: Abbott to Mohammad Hasnain, no run

Commentary: 130kph, perfect length, touch of shape away, he's squared up pushing to point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Warner, no run

Commentary: 132kph, good length angled in, it comes off the thigh pad

Commentary: full angled into leg, he pushes to mid on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Warner, no run

92kph, shorter, he's back and pulling to wide long on, they run brilliantly to pinch two

shorter length, he's back and punching to cover

length ball on middle, he swings hard but drags it off the inside edge through square leg. That was a proper mow
launched over square leg again! This has gone nearly 100m! Chest high short ball outside off, he's camped back and ready to swing hard. Again he flushed it

143kph, fuller outside off, he drives open chested to mid off

Commentary: 123kph, slower ball on leg, he chips this over midwicket without timing for a couple

Commentary: good length wide of off, he's back and running this to third man
142kph, short outside off, he's back and punching to deep point
driven through the offside

Commentary: short again. Warner watches it go by while fixing the umpire with a piercing look, who obliges and calls it awide
didn't middle this, flew through to deep cover, where Iftikhar was racing in. Falls slightly short though, meaning the possibility of a 10-wicket win is still very much on
stroked to mid-off
slower ball once more. Tidy over so far, this, but Australia just eight runs away
attempted pull by Finch, and the inside edge clips it onto his pads. He keeps the strike. Into the 12th over we go now
Finch thought about walloping this, but realised just in time he was getting a free run. 5 away from his half-century
misfield allows the Australian openers to come back for two. Four away from as eries win, each batsman three away from 50
brilliant stop at backward point from Shadab. He's an excellent fielder in that position, one of the best in the world, in truth
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Finch, no run

Commentary: low full toss, Finch drives through the air to long-on on the bounce. Right, three to win. Will Warner get his half-century instead, then?
not yet, nurdles it down to fine leg

and that brings it to an end! 50 for Finch, a series win for Australia. This is a blinding performance from the hosts against the world's number one team. They've made them look astonishingly pedestrian, and should do their confidence the world of good before the Test series. There's no sugar-coating this; Pakistan have been humbled here.
Commentary_short: Muhammad Musa to Finch, FOUR runs
